5000|$|In Greek, <b>the</b> <b>sermons</b> {{are called}} Kata Ioudaiōn (Κατὰ Ιουδαίων), which is {{translated}} as Adversus Judaeos in Latin and Against the Jews in English. The most recent scholarly translations, claiming that Chrysostom's primary targets {{were members of}} his own congregation who continued to observe the Jewish feasts and fasts, give <b>the</b> <b>sermons</b> <b>the</b> more sympathetic title Against Judaizing Christians.|$|R
