5000|$|<b>The</b> <b>sermons</b> {{inspired}} {{various people}} in the German Resistance. The Lübeck martyrs distributed <b>the</b> <b>sermons.</b> <b>The</b> <b>sermons</b> influenced <b>the</b> Scholl siblings in founding the White Rose pacifist student resistance group. One of Galen's sermons of 1941 was the group's first pamphlet. Generalmajor Hans Oster, a devout Lutheran and a leading member of the German Resistance, once said of Galen: He's a man of courage and conviction. And what resolution in his sermons! There should be a handful of such people in all our churches, {{and at least two}} handfuls in the Wehrmacht. If there were, Germany would look quite different! ...|$|R
